padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Privacy Based Oracle</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Equilibria is Monero fork; transactions are private and untraceable. This is extremely important for other privacy-based projects due to compatibility issues with other oracles.</p></div><div class="MuiGrid-root MuiGrid-item MuiGrid-grid-xs-12 MuiGrid-grid-md-6 MuiGrid-grid-lg-4"><img class="" height="50vh" src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin-right: 100%;"/><h3 style="font-size: 18px; padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Scalable Ecosystem</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">We designed every aspect of Equilibria\'s ecosystem to be scalable even with exponential growth. As usage of Pythia increases, more Oracle Nodes can join the network. In order to make a huge impact on the blockchain industry, we made sure Pythia can can handle thousands of Oracle Contracts.</p></div><div class="MuiGrid-root MuiGrid-item MuiGrid-grid-xs-12 MuiGrid-grid-md-6 MuiGrid-grid-lg-4"><img class="" height="50vh" src="/static/media/privateoraclessmall.67d5178e.png" style="margin-right: 100%;"/><h3 style="font-size: 18px; padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Decentralized Governance</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Just as anyone can mine Equilibria, anyone can run their own Oracle Node. Every Oracle Node is responsible for managing and making decisions for the tasks required of each Oracle Service. It is vital that anyone can start an Oracle Node to ensure no central entity is controlling the network or the blockchains utilizing Pythia.</p></div><div class="MuiGrid-root MuiGrid-item MuiGrid-grid-xs-12 MuiGrid-grid-md-6 MuiGrid-grid-lg-4"><img class="" height="50vh" src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin-right: 100%;"/><h3 style="font-size: 18px; padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Low Inflation/High Reward Tokenomics</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Pythia will help keep Equilibria\'s supply stable while maintaining a high incentive for further decentralization - there is a small fee attached to each Pythia transaction split 40/40/20. Oracle Nodes will receive 40% of the fees paid from Pythia. As the usage of Pythia increases, the ROI of running an Oracle Node will also increase. With a higher ROI comes a larger incentive to run an Oracle Node resulting in a more secure network. Another 40% of the fee is burnt to help stabilize the supply by offsetting the emission rate. The remaining 20% of the fee will go to the team and fund the project over the long-term.</p></div><div class="MuiGrid-root MuiGrid-item MuiGrid-grid-xs-12 MuiGrid-grid-md-6 MuiGrid-grid-lg-4"><img class="" height="50vh" src="data:image/png;base64," style="margin-right: 100%;"/><h3 style="font-size: 18px; padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Versatile Design</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Equilibria\'s oracle, Pythia, is capable of providing a solution to nearly any blockchain problem. Bringing data to the blockchain is difficult, but helping other blockchains decentralize their network protocols is even harder. Because of how versatile Pythia is, we can help other blockchains with problems ranging from price data to governance. Starting in early 2021, Pythia will become compatible with other blockchain types such as ETH and DOT so its services can be provided across the entire crypto ecosystem.</p></div><div class="MuiGrid-root MuiGrid-item MuiGrid-grid-xs-12 MuiGrid-grid-md-6 MuiGrid-grid-lg-4"><img class="" height="50vh" src="/static/media/opensourcepic.fce68fb7.png" style="margin-right: 100%;"/><h3 style="font-size: 18px; padding-top: 1vh; text-align: justify;">Open-Source</h3><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">It is important that the team\'s work is accessible for anyone to audit or contribute to. In January, 2021, a bounty program will be opened up to speed up development by adding incentives to contribute.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row" id="missionrow" style="padding-bottom: 20px;"><div style="width: 100%;
